text.tspan: Share of household consumption in GDP vs GDP per capita, 1950 to 2019
This data is adjusted for inflation and for differences in the cost of living between countries.
Data source: Feenstra et al. (2015), Penn World Table (2021)
Note: Saudi Arabia, Qatar, UAE and Kuwait are not shown. Each of these major oil exporters are characterised by a high GDP per capita and a very low household
